getDataStore

public DataStore getDataStore(DataStoreName name)
                       throws DataStoreNotFoundException
Obtains the DataStore that corresponds with the required name. If this DataStoreProvider can not provide the required data store a DataStoreNotFoundException is throw. To avoid receiving this exception consider use DataStoreProvider.isProviderDataStore(DataStoreName).
